type="external">erct-0014.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>f , g  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</fr:tex> be two dependent functions. A <fr:em><fr:strong>homotopy</fr:strong></fr:em> from <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>g</fr:tex>, writing <fr:tex>H \colon  f  \sim  g</fr:tex> is given by a dependent function <fr:tex>H \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</fr:tex>. We shall write <fr:tex>1_{ f } \colon  f  \sim  f</fr:tex> for the <fr:em><fr:strong>identity homotopy</fr:strong></fr:em> on <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> defined by <fr:tex>1_{ f } x: \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
