type="external">erct-000X.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>quasi-inverse</fr:strong></fr:em> to a function <fr:tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</fr:tex> equipped with homotopies <fr:tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</fr:tex>, rendering <fr:tex>g</fr:tex> simultaneously a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">section</fr:link> and a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex>f</fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <fr:tex>\eta</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>\epsilon</fr:tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <fr:em>unit</fr:em> and <fr:em>counit</fr:em> of the quasi-inverse.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2567</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-000W</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-000W.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Inverse</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>19</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda"
type="external">erct-000W.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>An <fr:em><fr:strong>inverse</fr:strong></fr:em> to a function <fr:tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:link
href="erct-000X.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000X">quasi-inverse</fr:link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <fr:tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</fr:tex> in <fr:tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</fr:tex> relating the (<fr:em>a priori</fr:em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> equipped with an inverse as an <fr:em><fr:strong>invertible function</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2569</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-003K</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-003K.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Embedding</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003K.agda"
type="external">erct-003K.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A function <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> is called an <fr:em><fr:strong>embedding</fr:strong></fr:em> when for any <fr:tex>x,y:A</fr:tex> the action on identifications <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x=y \to  fx=fy</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-000W.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000W">invertible</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
