expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>7954</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-001V</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-001V.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Naturality of <fr:link
href="erct-0014.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0014">homotopies</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001V.agda"
type="external">erct-001V.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>H  \colon  f  \sim  g</fr:tex> be a <fr:link
href="erct-0014.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0014">homotopy</fr:link> between two functions <fr:tex>f,g \colon  A  \to  B</fr:tex>. For any identification <fr:tex>p \colon  x =y</fr:tex> in <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>, we have an identification <fr:tex>H x  \cdot   \mathsf {act}_{ g } \, p =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \, p \cdot  Hy</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>7655</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#351</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-351.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-001V</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By identification induction on <fr:tex>p</fr:tex>, it suffices to show that <fr:tex>Hx \cdot \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl} \cdot  Hx</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>7956</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-001W</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-001W.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Naturality of <fr:link
href="erct-0014.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0014">homotopies</fr:link> onto the identity</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001W.agda"
type="external">erct-001W.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>H  \colon  f  \sim   1_{ A }</fr:tex> be a <fr:link
href="erct-0014.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0014">homotopy</fr:link> from <fr:tex>f \colon  A  \to  A</fr:tex> onto the identity function. Then we may construct a higher homotopy from <fr:tex>H \circ  f</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ  H</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>7675</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#350</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-350.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-001W</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex>x:A</fr:tex>, we must construct an identification from <fr:tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>. By the naturality (<fr:ref
addr="erct-001V"
href="erct-001V.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>) of <fr:tex>H</fr:tex> at the identification <fr:tex>H x \colon  f x = x</fr:tex>, we have an identification <fr:tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}   \cdot   \mathsf {act}_{ 1_{ A } } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  H x</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Simplifying, we have <fr:tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  H x =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  H x</fr:tex>; canceling <fr:tex>H x</fr:tex> on either side, we therefore have the desired identification <fr:tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
